# Pipeline & Verification Rules

## Scene schema (the contract everything consumes — do not change without a spec)
```ts
interface VideoTimeline {
  videoId: string;
  title: string;
  language: string;
  scenes: {
    id: number;
    narration: string;        // text sent to TTS
    audioUrl: string;         // per-scene mp3
    durationMs: number;       // measured from mp3, + 400ms padding
    visual: { type: 'bullet_card' | 'image' | 'diagram'; payload: unknown };
    onScreenText?: string;
  }[];
}
```
- Sync rule: scene display duration = its audio duration. Audio drives the timeline. Never hardcode durations.
- Measure mp3 duration with `music-metadata` server-side at generation time.

## ElevenLabs credit protection
- Hard budget guard: refuse synth if estimated chars would exceed remaining daily budget env `TTS_DAILY_CHAR_BUDGET`.
- Cache key: sha256(text + voiceId + model). Cache hit = zero credits.
- Demo scripts for the presentation are pre-generated and committed as fixtures.

## Remotion (export path only)
- One composition `<EduReel>` consuming `VideoTimeline` as inputProps; `<Sequence>` per scene with `<Audio>`.
- Render only on explicit "Export MP4" — never in the generation hot path.

## Playwright MCP sanity flow (Stage 6)
Run against `npm run dev`. The canonical flow, in order:
1. `/sign-up` → create user → expect redirect to profile setup
2. Select age group + ≥2 topics + ≥2 interests from chip catalogue → save
3. Profile page: assert widgets exist: total-time, topic-time, peak-hours, most-watched
4. Navigate to generate → pick topic+interest → submit → poll until player visible
5. Assert audio element plays and scene index increments at least once
6. After ≥10s playback, re-open profile → assert watch-time increased
- Selectors: use `testID` props (RN) which render as `data-testid` on web. Add them while building, not during verification.
- On any failure: capture screenshot + console via MCP, apply debugging-and-error-recovery, retry (max 3).
